{
  "stem": "21349.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we had a radio.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the radio, you had to scratch with a crystal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we listened to it, and they made a lot of noise.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were all very much upset that something bad is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But our non-Jewish neighbors, and I had a lot of friends there, they said to me, don't worry.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It will pass over.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were not so sure about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because then, when he came to power for seven days, they did nothing else, no work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were on a holiday.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They marched in the streets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They sang music, and they sang the song-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] about the people who were killed when Hitler made the putsch 10 years earlier in 1923, and they made a song which was called, which goes like this, translated from the German. 'When Jewish blood jumps off the knife, we feel twice as good.'",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the beginning, we didn't think much of emigrating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because my mother, especially, had all her relatives in Hamburg, and she didn't want to separate from them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as time went on, we thought more and more about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We started writing letters to the outside world, to others, whomever we could.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the answers were always negative.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First of all, as I said, in 1934 about a year after, I did not go to school anymore on Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they made this law that if you go, you have to do everything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I still had teachers from the time, from before Hitler, who were a little bit more human and understanding.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had a teacher who was already at that time 65 years old, close to retirement age at that time.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
